## Before building, read
- `architecture/build-context.md` — stack, conventions, where things live, patterns to follow/avoid
- `design-system/README.md` — tokens, components, states, accessibility standard
- `features/*.feature` — the verified behaviour to build to

## How to build here
- Build one story/feature at a time against its failing tests; "done" = tests pass (see the `build-implementation` skill).
- Use the design system's components and states; don't invent one-off UI.
- Honour the non-functional and security constraints in `architecture/constraints.md` and `architecture/threat-model.md`.
- Keep commits small and traceable to a story id.

